2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Suchitra%20Sen%20In%20%3Cem%3EAandhi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1975)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDirected%20by%20Gulzar%2C%20this%20was%20Suchitra%20Sen's%20last%20Hindi%20film.%20The%20film%20revolves%20around%20the%20chance%20meeting%20of%20an%20estranged%20couple.%20Aarti%20Devi%2C%20a%20prominent%20politician%2C%20finds%20herself%20staying%20in%20the%20hotel%20managed%20by%20her%20husband%20during%20an%20election%20campaign.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20movie%20faced%20an%20abrupt%20ban%20after%20running%20successfully%20for%20almost%2020%20weeks.%20The%20ban%20was%20due%20to%20the%20striking%20resemblance%20of%20Aarti%20Devi%2C%20with%20her%20elegant%20cotton%20sarees%20and%20silver%20streaks%2C%20to%20Indira%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20songs%20of%20the%20film%2C%20especially%20%3Cem%3ETum%20Aa%20Gaye%20Ho%20Noor%20Aa%20Gaya%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3ETere%20Bina%20Zindagi%20Se%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20are%20popular%20even%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20In%20%3Cem%3ESarkar%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2005)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20character%20of%20Subhash%20Nagre%2C%20portrayed%20by%20Big%20B%2C%20is%20loosely%20based%20on%20Vito%20Corleone%2C%20played%20by%20Marlon%20Brando%20in%20Francis%20Ford%20Coppola's%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Godfather%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20the%20film%2C%20Subhash%20Nagre%20runs%20a%20parallel%20government%20in%20Bombay%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20poor%20and%20the%20powerless.%20The%20character%20also%20bears%20a%20striking%20resemblance%20to%20Balasaheb%20Thackeray.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Abhishek%20Bachchan%20In%20%3Cem%3EDasvi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2022)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20father%20to%20son.%20A%20delightful%20dramedy%20about%20an%20uneducated%20and%20corrupt%20politician%20who%20decides%20to%20appear%20for%20his%20board%20examination%20from%20jail.%20All%20under%20the%20watchful%20eye%20of%20a%20stern%20police%20officer.%20Happy%20that%20I%20took%20time%20out%20to%20attend%20the%20premiere%20of%20the%20film.%20Spent%20a%20lovely%20three%20hours.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Alia%20Bhatt%20In%20%3Cem%3EGangubai%20Kathiawadi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPlaying%20the%20titular%20role%2C%20Alia%20Bhatt%20portrays%20the%20role%20of%20a%20prostitute%20who%20rises%20to%20power%20with%20panache.%20After%20winning%20the%20presidential%20elections%20in%20Kamathipura%2C%20she%20becomes%20a%20champion%20for%20women's%20rights.%20This%20story%20draws%20inspiration%20from%20Hussain%20Zaidi's%20book%20%3Cem%3EMafia%20Queens%20of%20Mumbai%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20her%20role%20in%20the%20film%2C%20Alia%20Bhatt%20received%20the%20National%20Award%20for%20Best%20Actress%20at%20the%2069th%20National%20Film%20Awards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Tigmanshu%20Dhulia%20In%20%3Cem%3EGangs%20of%20Wasseypur%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2012)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20cult%20classic.%20Tigmanshu%20Dhulia's%20dialogue%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BBeta%2C%20tumse%20na%20ho%20payega%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20became%20an%20instant%20hit%20and%20is%20still%20referenced%20in%20popular%20culture.%20Stand-out%20performances%20from%20all%20involved%3A%20Manoj%20Bajpayee%2C%20Nawazuddin%20Siddiqui%2C%20Huma%20Qureshi%2C%20Pankaj%20Tripathi%20and%20Rajkummar%20Rao.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Raveena%20Tandon%20In%20%3Cem%3ESatta%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2003)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaveena%20Tandon%20plays%20the%20role%20of%20a%20regular%20woman%20who%20steps%20into%20the%20world%20of%20politics%20after%20her%20politician%20husband%20is%20sent%20to%20jail%20on%20charges%20of%20murder.%20She%20navigates%20the%20dynamics%20of%20power%20politics%20and%20learns%20the%20art%20of%20survival.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Arun%20Sarnaik%20In%20%3Cem%3ESinhasan%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1979)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20Marathi%20film%2C%20written%20by%20Vijay%20Tendulkar%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20sharpest%20political%20dramas%20in%20the%20history%20of%20Indian%20cinema.%20Arun%20Sarnaik%20plays%20the%20role%20of%20a%20shrewd%20politician%20who%20is%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20Maharashtra.%20When%20he%20discovers%20that%20his%20rivals%20are%20plotting%20to%20unseat%20him%2C%20he%20announces%20a%20cabinet%20reshuffle.%20Schemes%20and%20machinations%20abound.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Anil%20Kapoor%20In%20%3Cem%3ENayak%3A%20The%20Real%20Hero%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2001)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Shivaji%20Rao%20Gaekwad%2C%20Anil%20Kapoor%20accepts%20a%20challenge%2C%20presented%20by%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20to%20govern%20the%20state%20for%20a%20day.%20In%20that%20one%20day%2C%20he%20takes%20steps%20to%20root%20out%20corruption%20from%20the%20system.%20He%20becomes%20so%20popular%20that%20he%20wins%20by%20a%20vast%20majority%20when%20he%20eventually%20contests%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E9.%20Mohanlal%20And%20Prakash%20Raj%20In%20%3Cem%3EIruvar%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(1997)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIruvar%2C%20regarded%20as%20one%20of%20Mani%20Ratnam's%20best%20works%2C%20portrays%20the%20friendship%20and%20political%20rivalry%20between%20M.G.%20Ramachandran%20and%20M.%20Karunanidhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EP.S.%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20has%20not%20only%20played%20the%20role%20of%20a%20politician%20in%20films%20like%20%3Cem%3ESarkar%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3EInquilaab%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20also%20contested%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20from%20Allahabad%20in%201984.%20He%20bagged%20a%20mammoth%2068%25%20of%20the%20votes%2C%20defeating%20former%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Chief%20Minister%20H.M.%20Bahuguna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Derek%20O'Brien%2C%20MP%2C%20leads%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20