tain%20View%2C%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6690f3379caa6ed01e00fe2e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIntuit%20is%20paying%20more%20than%20%24555%2C000%20in%20back%20wages%20to%20workers%20over%20missed%20overtime%20payments.%3Cp%3ESmith%20Collection%2FGado%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIntuit%20is%20paying%20more%20than%20%24555%2C000%20in%20back%20wages%20to%20workers%20who%20missed%20overtime%20payments.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Labor%20Department%20said%20it%20hadn't%20kept%20accurate%20pay%20records%20and%20didn't%20pay%20workers%20for%20required%20training.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20affected%20nearly%2015%25%20of%20its%20global%20workforce.%20The%20company%20this%20week%20announced%201%2C800%20job%20cuts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIntuit%2C%20a%20Silicon%20Valley%20company%20that%20provides%20financial%20software%20for%20employers%2C%20is%20paying%20back%20more%20than%20half%20a%20million%20dollars%20to%20thousands%20of%20its%20own%20workers%20after%20failing%20to%20pay%20them%20for%20some%20required%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20announcement%20came%20just%20a%20week%20before%20the%20company%20announced%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintuit-cuts-workers-not-meeting-expectations-hiring-in-other-areas-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaying%20off%2010%25%20of%20its%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Labor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dol.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Freleases%2Fwhd%2Fwhd20240702%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20early%20July%20that%20an%20investigation%20by%20its%20Wage%20and%20Hour%20Division%20had%20found%20that%20about%202%2C600%20US%20employees%20had%20collectively%20missed%20more%20than%20%24555%2C000%20in%20overtime%20pay%20because%20Intuit%20hadn't%20kept%20accurate%20pay%20records%20and%20hadn't%20paid%20workers%20for%20some%20time%20spent%20on%20required%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20Intuit%20failed%20to%20pay%20these%20workers%20the%20correct%20amount%20of%20overtime%20pay%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20one-and-a-half%20times%20normal%20wages%20for%20hours%20worked%20over%2040%20in%20a%20workweek%20%E2%80%94%20which%20violated%20the%20Fair%20Labor%20Standards%20Act%2C%20the%20DOL%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%202%2C610%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20all%20based%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20is%20getting%20between%20%2476%20and%20%24694%20each%20in%20back%20pay%2C%20with%20an%20average%20of%20about%20%24200%2C%20a%20DOL%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Based%20on%20its%20employee%20count%20of%20about%2018%2C000%20before%20the%20layoffs%2C%20this%20makes%20up%20nearly%2015%25%20of%20its%20global%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%2C%20which%20was%20settled%20administratively%2C%20covered%20the%20period%20from%20September%202021%20to%20July%202023%2C%20the%20DOL%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20who%20took%20QuickBooks%20ProAdvisor%20certification%20between%20September%202021%20and%20August%202023%20were%20notified%20that%20they%20would%20be%20compensated%20for%20the%20time%20they%20spent%20completing%20the%20course%20and%20they%20have%20now%20all%20been%20compensated%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Intuit%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20Intuit%20announced%20Wednesday%20that%20it%20was%20laying%20off%201%2C800%20employees%2C%20or%20about%2010%25%20of%20its%20workforce%2C%20including%201%2C050%20who%20it%20said%20weren't%20meeting%20performance%20expectations.%20Its%20CEO%20said%20that%20this%20wasn't%20down%20to%20cost-cutting%20measures%2C%20noting%20that%20Intuit%20planned%20to%20hire%20about%201%2C800%20more%20workers.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntuit%20also%20said%20that%20it%20would%20be%20closing%20two%20offices%3A%20one%20in%20Boise%20and%20