ki-class%20destroyer%20Suzutsuki%2C%20pictured%20here%20in%202019%2C%20sailed%20into%20Chinese%20waters%20on%20July%204%20for%20about%2020%20minutes.%3Cp%3ESTR%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJapan%20is%20investigating%20one%20of%20its%20naval%20destroyers%20after%20it%20sailed%20into%20Chinese%20waters%20near%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJapanese%20media%20reported%20that%20the%20incident%20occurred%20on%20July%204%20as%20China%20conducted%20live-fire%20drills.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAuthorities%20say%20it%20might%20have%20been%20a%20mistake%2C%20but%20are%20still%20questioning%20the%20warship's%20captain.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJapan's%20defense%20ministry%20is%20investigating%20officers%20of%20a%20naval%20destroyer%20that%20entered%20Chinese%20territorial%20waters%20for%20about%2020%20minutes%20on%20July%204%2C%20according%20to%20local%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.kyodonews.net%2Fnews%2F2024%2F07%2F28ac44dc7400-japan-destroyer-sailed-into-china-territorial-waters-despite-warnings.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKyodo%20News%20reported%20on%20Thursday%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Maritime%20Self-Defense%20Force%20destroyer%20Suzutsuki%20was%20monitoring%20Chinese%20live-fire%20drills%20on%20the%20coast%20of%20China's%20Zhejiang%20province%20when%20it%20pushed%20into%20Chinese%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhejiang's%20maritime%20authority%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.msa.gov.cn%2Fpage%2Farticle.do%3FarticleId%3D9E448C69-A56B-43EB-98DD-C251EF856FB6%26channelId%3D8E10EA74-EB9E-4C96-90F8-F891968ADD80%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissued%20a%20notice%20on%20July%203%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20it%20would%20conduct%20live-fire%20drills%20from%206%20a.m.%20on%20July%204%20to%2010%20p.m.%20the%20next%20day%2C%20designating%20a%20no-sail%20zone%20on%20the%20coast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20Kyodo%20News%2C%20the%20Suzutsuki%20approached%20the%20no-sail%20zone%20on%20July%204%20and%20was%20told%20by%20Chinese%20vessels%20to%20turn%20back%2C%20but%20accelerated%20and%20continued%20deeper%20into%20Chinese%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vessel%20was%20about%2012%20nautical%20miles%20from%20Zhejiang's%20coast%2C%20the%20outlet%20reported%2C%20citing%20two%20anonymous%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhejiang%20is%20one%20of%20mainland%20China's%20closest%20provinces%20to%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Suzutsuki%20departed%20Chinese%20waters%20about%2020%20minutes%20later%2C%20and%20Kyodo%20News%20sources%20said%20they%20suspected%20the%20accident%20may%20have%20been%20caused%20by%20a%20%26quot%3Bprocedural%20error.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Japanese%20authorities%20have%20yet%20to%20publicly%20explain%20exactly%20what%20caused%20the%20maritime%20incident.%20Kyodo%20News%20reported%20that%20the%20captain%20of%20the%20Suzutsuki%20is%20being%20questioned%20by%20Japan's%20defense%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fdepts%2Flos%2Fconvention_agreements%2Ftexts%2Funclos%2Fpart2.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternational%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20allows%20ships%20from%20one%20state%20to%20pass%20through%20another's%20territory%20as%20long%20as%20the%20vessel%20does%20not%20threaten%20the%20latter's%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20very%20least%2C%20there%20is%20no%20legal%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Japanese%20government%20official%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sankei.com%2Farticle%2F20240711-2HO757X2WZO5XOHNZXLCWBUOXE%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocal%20outlet%20Sankei%20Shimbun.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Kyodo%20News%20cited%20Chinese%20diplomatic%20officials%20saying%20that%20Beijing%20believes%20the%20Suzutsuki%20broke%20Chinese%20laws%20by%20failing%20to%20request%20entry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fjapan-navy-destroyer-enters-china-waters-near-taiwan-sparking-beijing-concerns-2024-07-11%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Chinese%20Foreign%20Ministry%20spokesperson%20Lin%20Jian%20said%20on%20Thursday%20that%20his%20office%20had%20lodged%20a%20complaint%20with%20Japan's%20government%20over%20the%20Suzutsuki's%20%26quot%3Billegal%20and%20improper%20actions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mod.go.jp%2Fmsdf%2Fequipment%2Fships%2Fdd%2Fakizuki%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESuzutsuki%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20Akizuki-class%20destroyer%2C%20which%20is%20about%20500%20feet%20long%20and%20can%20take%20a%20crew%20of%20about%20200.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sankei.com%2Farticle%2F20240711-UWCJKFVKGRLG7KXY6DR6N6YWQI%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESankei%20Shimbun%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20the%20destroyer%20was%20scheduled%20for%20several%20public%20viewings%20in%20Akita%2C%20Hachinohe%2C%20and%20Aomori%20throughout%20July%2C%20but%20these%20showings%20have%20since%20been%20canceled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%20of%20war%20between%20both%20nations%20because%20of%20this%20maritime%20incident%20is%20low%2C%20despite%20coming%20as%20Sino-Japanese%20relations%20remain%20tense%2C%20Ian%20Ja%20Chong%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20it%20doesn't%20seem%20that%20the%20PRC%20is%20really%20playing%20things%20up%20that%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chong%2C%20referring%20to%20China's%20full%20official%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJapan's%20investigation%20into%20the%20ship's%20captain%20may%20soothe%20China's%20indignance%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20gives%20Beijing%20an%20off-ramp.%20The%20issue%20is%20whether%20they%20want%20to%20take%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETokyo%20has%20also%20often%20noted%20China's%20incursions%20into%20its%20own%