ust%2020%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20special%20program%20allows%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-appears-use-faa-tool-block-jet-tracking-twitter-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eprivate%20jet%20owners%20to%20fly%20cloak%20their%20travels%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20using%20a%20temporary%20aircraft%20registration%20number.%20In%202022%2C%20Musk%20applied%20for%20a%20new%20aircraft%20registration%20number%20four%20times%2C%20JetSpy%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FAA%20first%20launched%20PIA%20in%202019.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20FAA%20told%20BI%20it%20had%20about%20390%20alternate%20ID%20codes%20since%20the%20program%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20Musk%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Dombroff%2C%20a%20partner%20and%20aviation%20attorney%20at%20Fox%20Rothschild%20LLP%20and%20a%20former%20FAA%20lawyer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it's%20unclear%20why%20Musk%20would%20begin%20using%20the%20program%20again%2C%20as%20the%20FAA%20has%20yet%20to%20make%20any%20apparent%20changes%20to%20it%20that%20could%20further%20benefit%20Musk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-who-tracks-elon-musk-jet-launching-own-website-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJet-tracking%20personality%20Jack%20Sweeney%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20the%20first%20to%20point%20out%20Musk's%20new%20PIA.%20The%20college%20student%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-private-jet-tracking-twitter-account-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egained%20popularity%20for%20his%20social%20media%20accounts%20that%20track%20celebrities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20Musk%20and%20Taylor%20Swift%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20Musk's%20team%20appeared%20to%20face%20some%20hiccups%20using%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThis%20recent%20implementation%20of%20PIA%20exposed%20its%20identity%20immediately.%20The%20PIA%20ICAO%20code%20was%20installed%2C%20but%20they%20then%20proceeded%20to%20broadcast%20N628TS%20as%20the%20callsign%20with%20the%20PIA%20then%20switch%20to%20a%20third%20party%20callsign.%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Jack%20Sweeney%20(%40Jxck_Sweeney)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJxck_Sweeney%2Fstatus%2F1807566969010282800%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%201%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20PIA%20program%20is%20far%20from%20perfect.%20According%20to%20the%20FAA%2C%20it%20allows%20aircraft%20owners%20to%20switch%20out%20their%20registration%20numbers%20every%2020%20days%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Fair_traffic%2Ftechnology%2Fequipadsb%2Fprivacy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elaborious%20process%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristian%20Renneissen%2C%20Collins%20Aerospace's%20manager%20for%20flight%20deck%20connectivity%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.avbuyer.com%2Farticles%2Fflight-dept-mgt%2Fbizav-privacy-how-to-fly-incognito-in-the-usa-113205%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epreviously%20told%20the%20trade%20publication%20AV%20Buyer%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20while%20the%20PIA%20program%20is%20essentially%20free%2C%20it's%20a%20hassle%20due%20to%20a%20substantial%20amount%20of%20paperwork.%20What's%20more%2C%20the%20entire%20process%20would%20have%20to%20start%20all%20over%20again%20if%20the%20new%20registration%20number%20is%20exposed%20and%20tied%20to%20the%20owner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlanes%20are%20also%20required%20to%20ditch%20the%20PIA%20for%20their%20permanently%20assigned%20ICAO%20address%20when%20they%20fly%20internationally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20PIA%20program%20limits%20the%20ability%20to%20identify%20an%20aircraft%20in%20real-time%20using%20inexpensive%2C%20commercially%20available%20receivers%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20FAA%20spokesperson%20previously%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThis%20does%20not%20prevent%20parties%20from%20using%20alternative%20methods%20(plane%20spotting%2C%20movement%20correlations%2C%20etc.)%20to%20identify%20PIA%20participants.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20growing%20security%20concerns%20from%20the%20likes%20of%20Musk%20and%20Swift%20prompted%20the%20FAA%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaylor-swift-elon-musk-private-jet-tracking-faa-reauthorization-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efurther%20its%20camouflage%20efforts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20thanks%20to%20new%20language%20in%20the%20FAA%20Reauthorization%20passed%20in%20May.%20This%20includes%20adding%20PIA%20protections%20for%20international%20flights%2C%20among%20other%20privacy%20enhancements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20still%20likely%20not%20enough%20to%20fully%20block%20private%20planes%20from%20the%20public%20view.%20Sweeney%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20celebrity%20private%20aircraft%20can%20still%20be%20spotted%20using%20context%20clues%2C%20such%20as%20the%20airports%20their%20jets%20commonly%20fly%20from.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-private-jet-flights-hidden-again-faa-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720774802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668fda7739de72f47bca3484%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-private-jet-flights-hidden-again-faa-2024-7