y%2012%20per%20cent%2C%20but%20the%20country%20will%20remain%20the%20world's%20most%20populous%20throughout%20the%20century%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Population%20Prospects%202024%20report%2C%20released%20here%20on%20Thursday%2C%20said%20that%20the%20world's%20population%20is%20expected%20to%20continue%20growing%20over%20the%20coming%2050-60%20years%2C%20reaching%20a%20peak%20of%20around%2010.3%20billion%20people%20in%20the%20mid-2080s%2C%20up%20from%208.2%20billion%20in%202024.%20After%20peaking%2C%20the%20global%20population%20is%20projected%20to%20start%20declining%20gradually%2C%20falling%20to%2010.2%20billion%20people%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20which%20surpassed%20China%20as%20the%20world's%20most%20populous%20nation%20last%20year%2C%20will%20continue%20to%20hold%20that%20position%20through%202100.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20population%20of%20India%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20remain%20the%20world's%20largest%20throughout%20the%20century%2C%20will%20likely%20decline%20by%2012%20per%20cent%20after%20reaching%20its%20peak%20in%20the%20early%202060s%20at%20about%201.7%20billion%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20UN%20report%20published%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20Department%20of%20Economic%20and%20Social%20Affairs%20(DESA)%2C%20Population%20Division%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20India's%20population%20in%202024%20is%20projected%20at%201.45%20billion%20and%20this%20will%20peak%20to%201.69%20billion%20in%202054.%20After%20this%2C%20India's%20population%20is%20projected%20to%20decline%20to%201.5%20billion%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20century%20in%202100%2C%20but%20the%20country%20will%20still%20remain%20the%20most%20populous%20nation%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20a%20question%20by%20PTI%20on%20population%20projections%20for%20India%2C%20Senior%20Population%20Affairs%20Officer%2C%20Population%20Division%2C%20UN%20DESA%20Clare%20Menozzi%20said%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20that%20%26quot%3BIndia%20is%20currently%20the%20largest%20country%20in%20the%20world%20in%20terms%20of%20population%2C%20and%20it%20is%20projected%20to%20stay%20so%20throughout%20the%20century.%20The%20population%20is%20currently%20estimated%20at%201.45%20billion%2C%20and%20it's%20supposed%20to%20increase%20further%26quot%3B%20to%201.69%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20supposed%20to%20peak%20around%20the%202060s%20in%20size%20and%20then%20it%20starts%20to%20slightly%20decline.%20So%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20century%2C%20India%20is%20projected%20to%20be%20around%201.5%20billion%2C%20but%20still%20the%20largest%20country%20in%20the%20world%20by%20a%20large%20margin.%26quot%3B%20The%20report%20said%20that%20China's%20population%2C%20currently%201.41%20billion%20in%202024%2C%20will%20fall%20to%201.21%20billion%20in%202054%20and%20further%20decline%20to%20633%20million%20by%202100.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20anticipated%20that%20China%2C%20the%20country%20currently%20with%20the%20world's%20second-largest%20population%2C%20will%20likely%20experience%20the%20largest%20absolute%20population%20loss%20between%202024%20and%202054%20(204%20million)%2C%26quot%3B%20followed%20by%20Japan%20(21%20million)%20and%20Russia%20(10%20million).%20%26quot%3BLonger-range%20population%20projections%20are%20more%20uncertain%26quot%3B%20for%20China%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20due%20to%20its%20large%20size%20and%20sustained%20low%20level%20of%20fertility%2C%20China%20is%20also%20likely%20to%20record%20the%20largest%20population%20decline%20of%20any%20country%20through%20the%20end%20of%20the%20century%20(786%20million%20people).%20By%202100%2C%20China%20is%20projected%20to%20have%20lost%20more%20than%20a%20half%20of%20its%20current%20population%20and%20to%20have%20returned%20to%20a%20population%20size%20comparable%20to%20that%20recorded%20in%20the%20late%201950s%20(50%20per%20cent%20probability).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20a%20question%20on%20the%20significantly%20low%20population%20projection%20for%20China%2C%20Director%20of%20the%20Population%20Division%20at%20UN%20DESA%20John%20Wilmoth%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20really%20relates%20to%20the%20level%20of%20fertility%20that's%20observed%20currently%20in%20China.%20The%20current%20number%20is%20right%20around%20one%20birth%20per%20woman%20on%20average%20over%20a%20lifetime.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20that%20you%20need%202.1%20births%20to%20maintain%20the%20current%20population%20without%20migration%2C%20if%20fertility%20levels%20remain%20at%20such%20a%20low%20level%2C%20even%20if%20they%20come%20up%20slightly%2C%20any%20fertility%20level%20if%20it's%20below%20two%2C%20or%20especially%20below%201.8%20or%20below%201.5%2C%20you're%20really%20getting%20into%20low%20levels%20of%20fertility%20and%20it%20produces%20a%20long%20run%20decline%20that's%20quite%20significant.%20And%20that's%20true%20for%20China.%20It's%20true%20for%20some%20other%20countries%20in%20this%20analysis%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilmoth%20said.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720765200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fjrmv5a_population-generic-india-ians_625x300_09_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findias-population-to-peak-in-early-2060s-to-1-7-billion-then-decline-un-6088019%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20population%20is%20projected%20to%20peak%20in%20the%20early%202060s%20at%20about%201.7%20billion%20and%20then%20decline%20by%2012%20per%20cent%2C%20but%20the%20country%20will%20remain%20the%20world's%20most%20populous%20throughout%20the%20century%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20has%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A