ery%20difficult%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%20a%20financially%20unstable%20family%2C%20Ghosh%20understood%20the%20importance%20of%20helping%20others%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20came%20to%20education.%20%E2%80%9CI%20had%20to%20work%20and%20struggled%20to%20get%20an%20education.%20If%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20work%20day%20and%20night%20to%20improve%20the%20system%20for%20the%20children%20of%20my%20village%2C%20then%20who%20will%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhosh%20has%20a%20BEd%20degree%20and%20a%20master%E2%80%99s%20in%20English%20and%20political%20science.%20%E2%80%9CI%20started%20working%20as%20a%20teacher%20in%201975%20and%20retired%20in%202008%20as%20an%20assistant%20teacher%20at%20Jamalpur%20High%20School%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ghosh%20was%20fresh%20out%20of%20college%2C%20ready%20to%20work%2C%20he%20had%20opened%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F125632%2Fteaching-chirag-school-rural-model%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20school%20for%20underprivileged%3C%2Fa%3E%20students%20with%20five%20of%20his%20friends.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20spirits%20were%20soon%20dulled%20by%20the%20financial%20burden%20I%20faced%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20personal%20funding.%20Working%20for%20the%20underprivileged%20meant%20lesser%20income%20for%20me.%20I%20became%20a%20family%20man%20and%20needed%20to%20support%20my%20family%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-22-1720614800.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%20Basantapur%20Junior%20High%20School%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-22-1720614800.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-22-1720614800-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-22-1720614800-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-22-1720614800-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-22-1720614800-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-356288%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%20Basantapur%20Junior%20High%20School%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnwillingly%20he%20stopped%20working%20for%20the%20school%20and%20looked%20for%20jobs%20elsewhere.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20school%20functioned%20for%20several%20years%20after%20that%20but%20I%20was%20not%20a%20part%20of%20it.%20It%20still%20haunts%20me%20that%20I%20had%20to%20put%20my%20needs%20before%20the%20school.%20But%20I%20was%20sure%20that%20I%20would%20get%20another%20chance%20to%20work%20for%20the%20society%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%20with%20a%20heavy%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opportunity%20came%20knocking%20on%20his%20door%20in%202008%20when%20Ghosh%20retired%20and%20decided%20to%20return%20to%20his%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98I%20still%20see%20hope%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Ghosh%20returned%20home%2C%20he%20realised%20that%20his%20village%20and%20the%20nearby%20villages%20still%20did%20not%20have%20any%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CChildren%20were%20travelling%20to%20different%20villages%20to%20study%2C%20and%20the%20dropout%20rate%20was%20quite%20high.%20Most%20students%20were%20economically%20disadvantaged%20with%20no%20options%20for%20a%20better%20education.%20These%20children%20not%20only%20came%20from%20poor%20homes%20but%20also%20belonged%20to%20scheduled%20castes%2C%20facing%20a%20lot%20of%20casteism%20and%20unfair%20discrimination%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhosh%20decided%20that%20he%20needed%20to%20do%20something.%20%E2%80%9CI%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20Government%20and%20raised%20the%20matter.%20I%20did%20all%20the%20research%20and%20then%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20State%20Government%20with%20the%20request%20of%20opening%20a%20junior%20high%20school%20in%20the%20village%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ghosh%20secured%20the%20approvals%20in%202010%2C%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20school%20did%20not%20start%20until%202014.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20know%20how%20government%20work%20is%20%E2%80%94%20slow%20as%20a%20snail.%20I%20dedicated%20all%20my%20time%20to%20getting%20the%20construction%20process%20started.%20The%20ruling%20party%20leaders%20at%20the%20time%20did%20not%20support%20me%20at%20all%2C%20but%20I%20had%20strong%20faith%20that%20everything%20would%20work%20out.%20Eventually%2C%20when%20the%20construction%20did%20start%2C%20it%20was%20the%20poor%20people%20of%20the%20village%20who%20helped%20me%20complete%20it%20quickly%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhosh%20faced%20another%20challenge%20when%20the%20school%20needed%20permanent%20teachers%20appointed.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20been%20struggling%20with%20no%20permanent%20teachers%20for%20years.%20Back%20then%2C%20I%20was%20faced%20with%20a%20dilemma%20%E2%80%94%20if%20I%20left%20the%20school%20without%20any%20permanent%20teacher%2C%20it%20would%20shut%20down.%20I%20have%20been%20working%20without%20a%20salary%20ever%20since%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-21-1720614806.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ghosh%20has%20been%20teaching%20for%20free%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20now.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F